    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Would be nice to have the Python C API call [`PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize`]( https://docs.python.org/3/c-api/unicode.html#c.PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize ) in [`cpython.unicode`]( https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/Cython/Includes/cpython/unicode.pxd ).",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "It's not really necessary. Simply do `buffer[:len].decode()`, which will do the same thing, via an inline function and then one line of `PyUnicode_Decode`. This way you can still pass an encoding and errors. `PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize` does a UTF8 decode anyway.",
